 Their childhoods were over. They were dying now. Earth was a tinhorn planet as far
 as they were concerned.
 When Trout and the theater manager, two tinhorns, said they didn't want any tinhorn
 fun, the dying children sauntered off, their feet sticking to the planet, coming unstuck,
