 "Hard times," said Trout.
 The manager told of being in on the development of a miraculous insulating material,
 which had been used on rocket ships to the Moon. This was, in fact, the same material
 which gave the aluminum siding of Dwayne Hoover's dreamhouse in Midland City its
 miraculous insulating qualities.
 The manager reminded Trout of what the first man to set foot on the Moon had said:
 "One small step for man, one great leap for mankind.''
 "Thrilling words," said Trout. He looked over his shoulder, perceived that they were
