 On the virgin planet, The Man was Adam and the sea was Eve.
 · The Man often sauntered by the sea. Sometimes he waded in his Eve. Sometimes he
 swam in her, but she was too soupy for an invigorating swim. She made her Adam feel
 sleepy and sticky afterwards, so he would dive into an icy stream that had just jumped
