 · Bunny was pale, the same unhealthy color of the blind fish that used to live in the
 bowels of Sacred Miracle Cave. Those fish were extinct. They had all turned belly-up
 years ago, had been flushed from the cave and into the Ohio River—to turn belly-up, to
 go bang in the noonday sun.
 Bunny avoided the sunshine, too. And the water from the taps of Midland City was
 becoming more poisonous every day. He ate very little. He prepared his own food in his
